item.title: How do you make a barrier?
item.dc:creator: @RandQm RandQm
item.description:
@RandQm wrote:

[quote=“Master Jrh1, post:9, topic:427257”][quote author=Team_Rocket link=topic=529955.msg3868783#msg3868783 date=1325189654]

You mean an invisible wall that spans a long distance? Or an object?

I’ve made something similar to the first one in the past. It’s honestly not worth it, it’ll make your server lag too much, even if you do it right. If you insist on it you can just call the coords like a Process method and use a forced-walk.

You got skype??? and show me what to do?

I mean for the barrier to go around the object point so when you try to go pass it, it will send you back to a certain co-ord I put in…

Search for the object ID in a list. Once you have it you can just add a condition for non-donators that make them do a forced-walk back to their original position.

Did I explain it well enough for you? Is there something I missed?

Am pretty new to all of this and I dont quite know where to fin
d it…

lmgtfy.com

LMGTFY

LMGTFY

You can use Google for ALOT of things that are server related. Just make sure that what you search for is related enough to RSPS.
[/quote]

Oh thanks lol I was looking for it inside my files for the private server, but now we go to the second step and I have no idea… facepalm[/quote]

He can but he’s obviously to lazy to do it himself,
google, searcg bar
tohard?
